# Tiebreak mode

A prior validator was uncertain. Re-check the unresolved component directly
from source and make the most specific supported decision. Do not convert
missing evidence, an incomplete search, or elapsed budget into a rejection.

- Promote only when every required component is independently verified.
- Reject only when a named source fact disproves a required component (for
  example, an effective guard, an unreachable constructor state, or a clearly
  non-shipping surface).
- Otherwise remain Uncertain and state exactly what evidence would settle it.
